<P>
   Another name making rounds is Virginia Tech's Frank Beamer. But
Beamer, a Tech alum, has a resume grounded in the South and
wouldn't appear to be the sort of fit Hedges wants.
</P>
<P>
   Others available include deposed Seahawks coach Dennis Erickson
and former Auburn coach Terry Bowden. But the pall over the '98
Seahawks likely would be among factors discouraging Hedges on
Erickson, while Bowden, like Beamer, would have to overcome
strictly Southern connections.
</P>
<P>
   Hedges, who expects to have a short list quickly, said she
wouldn't be opposed to pursuing a good candidate from the Pac-10
although she called that ``difficult.''
</P>
<P>
   Hedges said she would rely on an unnamed group of advisors to
assist in interviewing candidates, but that the decision will be
hers. She wouldn't specify when it will happen.
</P>
<P>
   Lambright earned a package of $566,000 including outside income,
and Hedges said, ``I would say the parameters would be similar.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
