<HEADLINE>
WHITE CASTLE, KRYSTAL HAMBURGER CHAINS AREN'T LINKED
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROGERS CADENHEAD 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Q: Two restaurant chains _ White Castle up north and Krystal in
the South _ sell identical hamburgers. Why does the company use two
different names?
</P>
<P>
   _ A.L.N., Fort Worth
</P>
<P>
   A: White Castle and Krystal are separate companies that both
specialize in small, square burgers topped with steamed onions.
</P>
<P>
   White Castle, which began in Wichita, Kan., became the first
hamburger chain in 1921. The company has about 340 restaurants in
10 states _ mostly in the Northeast.
</P>
<P>
   Krystal, which began 11 years later in Chattanooga, Tenn., has
around 340 restaurants in 10 Southern states, though none in Texas.
</P>
<P>
   The similarity between burgers hasn't been lost on the
companies. Krystal and White Castle have a verbal agreement not to
compete in the same cities, the Lexington Herald-Leader reported in
1996.
</P>
<P>
   Q: I'm looking for preserves made by a Trappist monastery. They
used to be sold at a store in downtown Fort Worth. Are they still
produced?
</P>
<P>
   _ H.L.K., Haslet, Texas
</P>
<P>
   A: Trappist Preserves have been made by monks at a Massachusetts
abbey since 1954. They also sell fruit and wine jellies, marmalade
and jam.
</P>
<P>
   For product information, call (508) 885-8730 or write to
Trappist Abbey Gifts, St. Joseph's Abbey, Spencer, MA 01562-1233.
</P>
<P>
   You also can order Trappist Preserves online at
www.spencerabbey.org/preserves.
</P>
<P>
   Q: What has happened to S&AMP;H Green Stamps? I have nine books and
don't know what to do with them.
</P>
<P>
   _ M.C., Fort Worth
</P>
<P>
   A: Most stamps are redeemed today through the Sperry &AMP;
Hutchinson mail-order catalog.
</P>
<P>
   To receive the free catalog, call the National Mail Order Center
at (800) 435-5674 or write to National Mail Order Center, Box 5775,
Norcross, GA 30091-5775.
</P>
<P>
   (Rogers Cadenhead writes a trivia column for the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram. He can be reached at the Star-Telegram, Box 1870,
Fort Worth, Texas 76101; or by E-mail at trivia(at)prefect.com.
Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com)
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-12-31-98 1324EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
