<P>
   NATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   PBP_GO SMOKE (DEVELOPING) _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ So who are
these doctors who are fighting for Ed Holloway's right to smoke in
a Palm Beach County building as he works as a planner? Holloway,
who has two forms of cancer, says he suffers from post-traumatic
stress from his tour of duty in Vietnam. He got some doctors to say
that he needs to smoke. So is their opinion supported by medical
thought on the subject? And what can the Army tell us about
Holloway and his tour in Vietnam? (Moffett, Palm Beach Post)
</P>
<P>
   PBP_WE SMOKE _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ A visit to the front
lines of the smoking wars. How do the county workers forced outside
to light up feel about their persecution by the majority? And what
do non-smokers think about the enemy? (Hayes, Palm Beach Post)
</P>
<P>
   PBP_CHILD SEAT _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ A new University of
Florida study of child safety seats found that 95 percent of
children aren't strapped in correctly _ and greater danger for
injury or death in a car accident. The statewide study, funded by
the Florida Department of Transportation, examined more than 1,500
safety seats in vehicle inspections during the past year. The main
problem is parents failing to use a metal locking clip on the child
seat, which prevents the seat from being thrown forward in the
event of a collision. (Banstetter Palm Beach Post)
</P>
<P>
   AUS-Y2K-COMPUTER-BUG_ The Millennium Bug could start a preview
of disaster today, as some computers that don't recognize years
that begin with anything other than 19 try to update their internal
calendars by looking ahead one year and trip over Jan. 1, 2000.
They could crash or, more likely, begin spewing erroneous
information. What kind of computers? Probably not those that
operate Austin's services, such as water or electricity, police,
fire or EMS. Officials are on top of those. More likely the cash
registers or accounting systems of small businesses that haven't
been able to afford Y2K fixes. State, city and UT experts say we'll
have to wait and see. (Stanley, American-Statesman)
</P>
<P>
   w/AUS-Y2K-BOX _ Brace yourself for the six other Y2K preview
dates in 1999. (Austin, American-Statesman)
</P>
<P>
   SOUTH-WEATHER _ NASHVILLE _ Tennessee and other Southern
mountain states were expected to be slapped by another winter storm
_ even as some residents were still digging out from the one last
week. At least 900 families in the Nashville area still were
without electricity. (DuBose, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
(FREELANCER, not for use by NYT News Service)
</P>
<P>
   LOSNINOS-WEATHER _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ Is this how global
warming announces itself and claims retribution for burning fossil
fuels and leveling forests? Or did we just get caught in a nasty
family tug-of-war between a robust El Nino and La Nina? A look at
what the experts say. (McLachlin, Palm Beach Post) MOVED
