English-speaking countries throughout the world. Thus, while Barnes
&AMP; Noble and Amazon.com are battling over the so-far unprofitable
spoils of the Internet, Borders is investing in terra firma. It
approach has cheered some investors but also has raised doubts
among some analysts who wonder whether the chain has moved too
slowly to invest in electronic commerce. By Doreen Carvajal. (1650
words)
