<P>
   MURDER-RATE (Washington) _ The nation's murder rate fell in 1997
to its lowest level in three decades, with the bulk of the decline
occurring in large cities, the Justice Department says. The sharp
increase in the late 1980s and the decline in the 1990s stem from
the rise and fall in gun violence by younger Americans. By ERIC
ROSENBERG. (For release Saturday at 4:30 p.m.).
</P>
