   MEANS-COLUMN (Washington) _ A bipartisan consensus is emerging
that if President Clinton is not convicted in a Senate trial, he
should be censured with some punishment that goes beyond verbal
chastisement. It's called censure plus. But finding a politically
acceptable way to give Clinton an extra kick when he's down is
complicated. By MARIANNE MEANS.
