<HEADER>
A3627 &Cx1f; ttj-z
u d &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-FOOD-CHOCOLATE-RECIPE     12-31 0936
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FOOD-CHOCOLATE-RECIPES-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
SUPERNATURAL BROWNIES 

</HEADLINE>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 
(Eds.: See Food-Chocolate)
<TEXT>
<P>
   From ``Chocolate: From Simple Cookies to Extravagant
Showstoppers'' by Nick Malgieri (HarperCollins, $40). Although the
name sounds like an exaggeration, you'll agree that these brownies
are absolutely out of this world.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
2 sticks unsalted butter, plus more for greasing pan &QL; 
8 ounces bittersweet or semisweet chocolate, cut into 1/4-inch
pieces &QL; 
4 large eggs &QL; 
1/2 teaspoon salt &QL; 
1 cup each: granulated sugar and firmly packed dark brown sugar &QL; 
2 teaspoons vanilla extract &QL; 
1 cup flour &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Set a rack at the middle level of the oven and preheat to 350
degrees. Prepare a 13-by-9-by-2-inch pan: Grease inside of pan with
butter. Line pan with parchment or foil; grease parchment with
butter.
</P>
<P>
   Bring pot with 3 inches of water to a boil; turn off heat. Place
2 sticks butter and chocolate in small, deep stainless-steel bowl;
set bowl in water. Stir until butter and chocolate melt.
</P>
<P>
   Alternatively, boil water in bottom pot of double boiler; turn
off heat. Place butter and chocolate in top pot. Or place butter
and chocolate in microwave-safe bowl and microwave on medium,
stopping every 30 seconds to stir, until butter and chocolate are
melted. (Melted chocolate will hold its shape in the microwave, so
stirring frequently is essential to prevent burning.)
</P>
<P>
   Whisk eggs together in a large bowl, then whisk in salt, sugars
and vanilla. Stir in chocolate mixture, then fold in flour.
</P>
<P>
   Pour batter into pan and spread evenly. Bake 45 minutes until
top forms a shiny crust and batter is moderately firm. Cool in pan
on a rack. Wrap pan with plastic wrap and keep at room temperature,
or refrigerate it until the next day.
</P>
<P>
   To cut brownies, invert pan onto a cutting board, remove
parchment, and place a second cutting board on top. Turn brownies
right-side-up and trim away edges. Cut brownies into 2-inch
squares. Serve brownies on their own, with ice cream or with a hot
fudge sauce. To store, wrap brownies individually and keep at room
temperature in a tin or plastic container with a tight-fitting lid.
Or freeze them.
</P>
<P>
   Makes 24 brownies. If you have a 12-by-18-by-2-inch commercial
half-sheet cake pan, this recipe doubles easily.
</P>
<P>
   Variation: Add 2 cups chopped walnuts or pecans (1/2 pound) to
the batter.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL; 
CRISP CHOCOLATE BISCOTTI &QL; 
 &QL; 
From ``Chocolate.'' This is based on a recipe by Ellen Baumwoll,
proprietor of Bijoux Doux in New York City.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
1 3/4 cups all-purpose flour &QL; 
2/3 cup alkalized (Dutch process) unsweetened cocoa powder &QL; 
2 teaspoons baking powder &QL; 
Pinch of salt &QL; 
1 1/4 cups sugar &QL; 
1 1/2 cups chopped skinned hazelnuts or walnuts &QL; 
4 large eggs &QL; 
1 teaspoon vanilla extract &QL; 
 &QL; 
Set rack at middle level of oven and preheat to 325 degrees. Line 2
baking sheets or jelly-roll pans with parchment or foil. Mix flour,
cocoa, baking powder and salt; sift mixture into a mixing bowl.
Stir in sugar and hazelnuts.
</P>
<P>
   Whisk eggs and vanilla together, and stir into flour mixture to
form a dough. On a lightly floured surface, press dough together.
Divide dough in half, and roll each half into a log nearly the
length of the pan (14 to 18 inches). Place each log on a pan, and
flatten slightly. Bake 30 minutes, until logs have risen and are
firm. Cool logs in pans.
</P>
<P>
   After logs have cooled, lift them from parchment and diagonally
cut each into 1/2-inch-thick slices with a serrated knife. Place
biscotti, cut side down, on parchment-lined pans, and bake another
20 minutes until dry and crisp. Cool in pans.
</P>
<P>
   Serve biscotti with coffee, ice cream or red wine. Store in a
tin or plastic container with a tight-fitting lid. Makes about 4
dozen biscotti.
</P>
<P>
   Variation: For Chocolate Espresso Biscotti, add 3 tablespoons
instant espresso powder to flour mixture.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL; 
INSTANT CHOCOLATE MOUSSE &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   From ``Chocolate.'' This dessert is ready in only a few minutes;
it needs only time to chill before serving.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
1 (16-ounce) bar bittersweet chocolate &QL; 
1 cup whipping cream &QL; 
2 tablespoons dark rum, other liquor or strong coffee &QL; 
4 egg whites &QL; 
1/2 cup sugar &QL; 
 &QL; 
Use a paring knife or vegetable peeler to shave 6 curls of
chocolate from bar. Chop chocolate bar into 1/4-inch pieces. In
heavy saucepan over medium heat, bring cream to boil. Remove from
heat. Add chocolate; let stand a few minutes. Whisk mixture until
smooth, and pour into a large bowl. Whisk rum into mixture; cool to
room temperature. Do not allow to solidify; if it does, warm bowl
briefly in a larger bowl of warm tap water and stir smooth with a
rubber spatula.
</P>
<P>
   When mixture has cooled, combine egg whites and sugar in mixer
bowl and place over a pan of simmering water, whisking constantly,
until egg whites are hot and sugar has dissolved. Use electric
mixer to whip into a meringue; mixture will cool and inflate in
volume. Do not overbeat, or egg whites will become dry.
</P>
<P>
   Fold meringue into chocolate mixture, and spoon into 6 stemmed
glasses or (6-cup) serving bowl. Garnish with chocolate shavings
just before serving. Makes about 1 quart mousse (6 generous
servings).
</P>
<P>
   Variations:
</P>
<P>
   Instant Milk Chocolate Mousse: Substitute milk chocolate for
bittersweet chocolate. Decrease sugar to 1/4 cup.
</P>
<P>
   Instant White Chocolate Mousse: Substitute white chocolate for
bittersweet chocolate. Decrease sugar to 1/4 cup.
</P>
<P>
   Striped Parfaits of Chocolate Mousse: In stemmed glasses,
alternate layers of white, milk and dark chocolate mousses. Garnish
with mixed white, milk and dark chocolate shavings.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
XXXX END OF STORY &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
