<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-31 16:35 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A3791 &Cx1f; tic-z
r e &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-MOVIES98-WORST-AZR &LR;      12-31 0546
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-MOVIES98-WORST-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
IT CAME FROM HOLLYWOOD: YEAR'S LEMON CROP  
 (ADV: WITH MOVIES98 AND MOVIES98-BEST) 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By BOB FENSTER  
 c.1998 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   PHOENIX - Here's a list of the worst movies of 1998:
</P>
<P>
   1. ``Fear and Loathing in Las Vegas'' _ Johnny Depp stars as a
fictionalized version of writer Hunter Thompson going through a
mental meltdown on a drug binge. This gross comedy of dementia
makes you feel like signing up for a detox program even if you've
never done drugs.
</P>
<P>
   2. ``Tarzan and the Lost City'' _ You can picture the story
conference at the movie studio: ``Hey boss, we've got the extra
loincloth and $14.95 for special effects. Let's make another Tarzan
movie!''
</P>
<P>
   How bad is this one? The rubber snake is the best actor in the
cast.
</P>
<P>
   3. ``Two Girls and a Guy'' _ A guy (Robert Downey Jr.) gets
caught deceiving two girlfriends, and they take turns yelling at
him for the entire movie. Sitting through this shrill scolding is
like being trapped in a motel room with thin walls and listening to
some other couple's screaming fit.
</P>
<P>
   4. ``Orgazmo'' _ This laughless sex farce, about a missionary
who becomes a porn star, comes from ``South Park's'' Trey Parker,
who is exploring to what extent he can insult the intelligence of
his fans and still take their money. Its NC-17 rating apparently
means that anyone with an IQ of more than 17 doesn't qualify.
</P>
<P>
   5. ``Sphere'' _ A science-fiction mystery so murky that half the
time you don't know what you're seeing and the other half you don't
know what they're thinking. Bonus points for the most unlikely
casting of the year: pairing Dustin Hoffman with Sharon Stone.
</P>
<P>
   6. ``Slappy and the Stinkers'' _ In a year of great kid movies,
there's still a stinker, and this tale of cute kids and a sea lion
is it. With its flying food, body odor, toilet and barf jokes to
amuse the kiddies, the movie must have started hundreds of family
fights over which parent took the kids to see it and which was
lucky enough to regrout the bathroom tile instead.
</P>
<P>
   7. ``Hush'' _ Jessica Lange goes nuts as the psycho
mother-in-law from hell in a thriller that plods along with the
pace of a bad head cold. You know you'll get over it sometime, but
it doesn't feel like any time soon.
</P>
<P>
   8. ``Senseless'' _ Marlon Wayans and David Spade team up in a
college comedy full of scratching and body-piercing jokes. Well,
not jokes exactly. References. ``Senseless'' is so flat and devoid
of anything approaching fun that it seems cruel to pick on it.
</P>
<P>
   9. ``Palmetto'' _ An addled attempt to create the passion of
``Body Heat's'' wave of sex and crime. But Woody Harrelson and
Elisabeth Shue aren't sweating out of passion. They're sweating out
the bad directing and writing.
</P>
<P>
   10. ``Lost in Space'' _ Basic rule of bad science-fiction
movies: When you have no idea what you're doing, jack up the sound
effects.
</P>
<P>
   This attempt to turn the camp TV show into a serious adventure
movie is so brainless you could hear the explosions two theaters
over.
</P>
<P>
   Five films that would have made the worst list if we counted by
15s instead of 10s: ``Zero Effect,'' `` Small Soldiers,'' ``Let's
Talk About Sex,'' ``Rush Hour,'' ``What Dreams May Come.'' &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
