<TEXT>
<P>
   The Seattle Post-Intelligencer plans to move the following for
clients of the NYTimes News Service for editions of Friday, Jan. 1,
and thereafter. If you have any questions, please call Bob Schenet
at (206) 448-8037.
</P>
<P>
   FILM-1998 (Undated) _ What worked and didn't work in a year of
movies _ a variety of lists, picks and pans.
</P>
<P>
   By William Arnold. (Story has moved in the ``e'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   TV-1998 (Undated) _ Spawning a hit show isn't easy. TV series
fail for all sorts of reasons. Bad writing. Bad acting. Bad
scheduling. Bad breath. Even bad lettering can doom a promising
show.
</P>
<P>
   By John Levesque. (Story has moved in the ``e'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   FBC-HUSKIES (Seattle) _ The search is on for Jim Lambright's
replacement as football coach at the University of Washington.
</P>
<P>
   By Bud Withers. (Story will move in the ``s'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   VECSEY-COLUMN (Undated) _ Post-card memories from the sports
year, including Nagano, spring training, George Karl and the
record-breaking feats of Ken Griffey Jr. and Alex Rodriguez.
</P>
<P>
   By Laura Vecsey. (Story will move in the ``s'' category.)
</P>
